body: @ed728  Thanks! But this issue is may personal opinion. I think we would better get other members' comments before diving into this issue.

Looking at the file I also believed it to be way too large and way too unreadable. I think it should be split logically based on Operator type. The current WIP commit will not pass tests as the imports are still wonky, but that is a quick fix if people believe this issue is worth finishing.
@tkng @yd8534976

issue.title: Refactored operators. (#532)

Based on #532. 
## Description
<!--- 📝🎯📝 Describe your changes in detail. 📝🎯📝 -->
The operators have been split and organised into multiple files as demonstrated below.
```
from base import Operator
from convpool import Conv, Pool, Maxpool, AveragePool
from math import Add, Gemm, Mul, Maximum, MatMul, Minimum
from misc import Identity, BatchNormalization, Dropout, Unique, Cast, Prod, BatchNormalizationOptimized
from output import Softmax, Rely, LeakyRelu
from quantization import Quantizer, QTZ_binary_mean_scaling, QTZ_linear_mid_tread_half, QTZ_binary_channel_wise_mean_scaling, Lookup
from shape import SpaceToDepth, Transpose, Reshape, Flatten, ConcatOnDepth, DepthToSpace, ResizeNearestNeighbor, Split, Pad, Shape, StridedSlice
from variable import Variable, Input, Constant, Output
```

The above code is from a newly created `__init__.py` which should keep the API as it has been.
